comments.content:
@James Eduardo Recife does some really cool type faces.

When I was reading about Burgues it said that it was '[an] ode to the late 19th century American calligrapher Louis Madarasz' and that got me thinking about how contemporary it is. But I have seen other scripts such as for this cloths company [All Saints](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020153731/http:/www.allsaintsshop.co.uk/) that I consider to have quite an old skool look but still contemporary - so I know where you are coming from when you say it is subjective.

@Florian Yeah and anything like this: [My Fonts](http://web.archive.org/web/20131020153731/http:/www.allsaintsshop.co.uk/)

@Nick Interesting the use of the pseudo-randomization. It does look contemporary. It doesn't do much for me though.
